Experiment 4: Distance Monitoring System with RGB LED, Servo Motor and Buzzer

Description:
This experiment combines an ultrasonic sensor, servo motor, RGB LED and buzzer to create a complete proximity monitoring
 and warning system.

The RGB LED provides visual feedback, the servo motor responds mechanically to distance changes,
 and the buzzer activates when an object enters a critical distance range.

Code Logic:

-Safe Zone

Distance > 30 cm
RGB LED = Green
Servo = 180°
Buzzer = OFF

-Warning Zone

Distance between 15 cm and 30 cm
RGB LED = Yellow
Servo = 90°
Buzzer = OFF

-Critical Zone

Distance < 15 cm
RGB LED = Red
Servo = 0°
Buzzer = ON

Features:

-Real-time distance measurement
-Visual warning through RGB LED
-Audible warning through buzzer
-Mechanical response through servo motor
-Multi-device integration using a single sensor

Real-Life Applications:

-Obstacle detection systems in robotics and autonomous vehicles.
-Collision warning systems in parking and vehicle assistance applications.
-Restricted area monitoring where an alarm is triggered if someone comes too close.
-Security systems that provide visual and audible alerts when movement is detected.
-Industrial safety systems that warn operators before entering hazardous zones.
-Smart manufacturing environments where machines can react to worker proximity.
-Assistive technology for visually impaired individuals, using sound alerts when obstacles are nearby.

Project Outcome:
This final experiment demonstrates how a single sensor can control multiple output devices simultaneously.
The system provides mechanical, visual, and audible feedback based on object proximity,
 making it a practical introduction to embedded systems, automation, smart sensing,
  and safety monitoring applications.